Hi

I meet one problem about missing prefix for unique statement argument if the leaf is in side one container. My yang module like this:
```
    sudmodule test {
        grouping list-group {
            list l {
                unique "b/c";
                container b {
                    leaf c {
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
```
In the generated sch file, the unique statement argument is translated to "$pref:b/c", but the correct one should be "$pref:b/$pref:c".

I checked the dsdl.py, if unique statement is inside grouping, the "$pref:" is added by gen-schematron.xml when generate sch file.
```
  <xsl:template name="qname">
    <xsl:param name="name" select="@name"/>
    <xsl:if test="not(contains($name,':'))">$pref:</xsl:if>
    <xsl:value-of select="$name"/>
  </xsl:template>
```
In this case, the name value is "b/c".

Hi, Davis!
I made my own face detector using dlib dnn. I noticed that the performance of the detector falls dramatically if you feed images of different sizes. Moreover, in this case, it is not possible to efficiently parallelize the calculations on multiple gpus. As a result of profiling it became clear that the reason for the slowdown lies in the frequent calls of cudaMallocHost() function. I solved this problem by changing the method resizable_tensor::set_size(...) as follows:

```
diff --git a/dlib/dnn/tensor.h b/dlib/dnn/tensor.h
index 80d51ef..bcbb700 100644
--- a/dlib/dnn/tensor.h
+++ b/dlib/dnn/tensor.h
@@ -385,7 +385,8 @@ namespace dlib
             m_nr = nr_;
             m_nc = nc_;
             m_size = n_*k_*nr_*nc_;
-            data_instance.set_size(m_size);
+            if (data_instance.size() < m_size)
+                data_instance.set_size(m_size);
 #ifdef DLIB_USE_CUDA
             cudnn_descriptor.set_size(m_n,m_k,m_nr,m_nc);
 #endif
```

Is it the best way to solve this problem?

